HEADWORD: Nelumbo
<hw>Ne*lum"bo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[Ceylonese
word.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of great water lilies. The
North American species is <spn>Nelumbo lutea</spn>, the Asiatic is the
sacred lotus, <spn>Nelumbo speciosa</spn>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Nelumbium</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

